    "updated_at": "2024-11-19T03:05:25Z",
    "body": "@eggbean Starship does support it. And it works in PowerShell, but not as complete as it could be.\r\nFor example, notice the red dash on the right edge of the terminal, indicating that the command `nuget foo` failed (just bellow `23:39:38`:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/384a9774-7edb-4901-84a9-0f025073fb52)\r\n\r\nThis is in Windows Terminal, different terminals support different features.\r\n\r\nFor example, when you right click on a command, you can copy its output:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d281c093-a564-4c39-b036-88350e1f9f1f)\r\n\r\nSee other features here:\r\nhttps://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/terminal/tutorials/shell-integration#shell-integration-features",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
